data.p: Mary engaged with Joseph
An angel tells Joseph that Mary will have a baby.
The angel says to name it Jesus
The angel told Mary not to be afraid
The angel also said the baby would have great power
Mary visited her relative, Elizabeth
Elizabeth was pregnant
Mary greeted Elizabeth with the news
The baby growing in Elizabeth jumped for joy
Elizabeth said Mary was blessed
Mary sang about it
She sang about how her baby would help the Lord
She thanks the Lord in her song
She thought Jesus would overthrow great kings
She also thanked the Lord about helping her desendants
Mary remained with Elizabeth for three months
Elizabeth gave birth to a son named John
John grew up and became a baptist
The Emperor called for a census
Joseph was going to Bethlahem for the census
Mary was to go with him
In Bethlahem, it was time to have the baby
An angel told nearby shepards that a special baby would be born
Mary gave birth to Jesus
